        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 21 at 3:16PM EDT by NWS Cleveland OH</headline>
        <description>At 315 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Edinboro to near Adamsville. Movement was
northeast at 60 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph, torrential downpours and pea size
hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor flooding is possible in areas of
poor-drainage.

Locations impacted include...
Meadville, Corry, Edinboro, North East, Union City, Cambridge
Springs, Waterford, Wattsburg, Adamsville, Canadohta Lake, Riceville,
Harmonsburg, Lincolnville, Guys Mills, Atlantic, Saegertown, Conneaut
Lake, Mill Village, Blooming Valley, and Townville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
